collections framework->a collection represents a group of objects In java collections provide classess and interfaces for us to be able to write code quickly and efficiently

why we need collections:
->we need collections for efficient storage and better manipulation of data in java
for eg:we use arrays to store integers but what if we want 
resize this array?
insert an element in between?
delete an element in array?
apply certain operations to change this array?

How are collections are available?
Collections in java are available as classess and interfaces.Following are few commonly used collections in java:
1.ArrayList->for variable size collections
2.Set->for distinct collections
3.Stack-> a lifo data structure
4.HashMap-> for storing key value pairs

collections class is available in java.util package Collections class also provides static methods for sorting,searching etc.
 